\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
System Overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 This system is designed to completely replace Keyboard Maestro\'92s native "Prompt for User Input" action, offering significantly greater formatting flexibility, faster rendering, and much richer data processing capabilities.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The system relies on a clean, modular architecture:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Configuration:
\f1\b0  You define your prompt's layout, buttons, text fields, and hotkeys using a simple, human-readable JSON file.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Compilation:
\f1\b0  A Python-based rendering engine converts that JSON file into a highly styled, responsive HTML interface. Because this compilation can happen 
\f2\i before
\f1\i0  run-time, the prompt appears on screen instantly when called.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Execution:
\f1\b0  A a Prompt via HTML Action displays the compiled HTML file.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Data Return:
\f1\b0  Upon user interaction, the prompt natively updates any specified Keyboard Maestro text variables, closes, and returns a rich string containing: the \cf3 \cb4 id\cf2 \cb1  of the selected button, a string of any keyboard \cf3 \cb4 modifiers\cf2 \cb1  held, the specific \cf3 \cb4 key\cf2 \cb1  pressed, and an optional custom \cf3 \cb4 param\cf2 \cb1  value.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Features Overview
\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 UI & Formatting Setup
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Multi-Row Layouts:
\f1\b0  Organize elements into horizontal rows, with optional left-aligned descriptive labels for clean, grid-like alignment.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Visual Grouping:
\f1\b0  Add customizable horizontal line separators (thin, thick, dotted, and colored) above or below any row.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Item Types:
\f1\b0  Supports clickable buttons, passive text phrases, invisible structural placeholders, and interactive text input fields.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Custom Styling:
\f1\b0  Highlight specific buttons with colored borders, apply font styles (bold/italics), and set custom background colors for the entire window.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Configuration Metadata:
\f1\b0  Built-in display for the configuration name and version number to easily track your UI iterations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Interaction & Key Handling
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Rich Data Return:
\f1\b0  Upon submission, passes four distinct variables back to Keyboard Maestro for routing: the button 
\fs26 id
\fs24 , the 
\fs26 modifiers
\fs24  held, the specific 
\fs26 key
\fs24  pressed, and an optional custom 
\fs26 param
\fs24 .\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Advanced Key Mapping:
\f1\b0  Assign multiple distinct triggers to a single button using comma-separated lists (e.g., 
\fs26 m, M, f1
\fs24 ) or ranges (e.g., 
\fs26 1-9
\fs24 , 
\fs26 a-z
\fs24 ).\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Smart Modifier Fallbacks:
\f1\b0  Any button can accept any modifier natively. For example, pressing 
\f3\fs26 \uc0\u8984 
\f1 R
\fs24  will successfully trigger the 
\fs26 r
\fs24  button while passing the 
\f3\fs26 \uc0\u8984 
\f1\fs24  modifier back to Keyboard Maestro, 
\f2\i unless
\f1\i0  a dedicated 
\f3\fs26 \uc0\u8984 
\f1 R
\fs24  button explicitly exists to intercept it.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Hybrid Input System:
\f1\b0  Seamlessly mixes single-key command triggers with standard text input fields. The script automatically pauses hotkeys when an input field is focused (Edit Mode) and restores them the moment you click away or press Enter/Escape (Command Mode).\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Standard Dialog Behaviors:
\f1\b0  Supports UI standards like designated Default (Enter) and Cancel (Escape) buttons, Tab-cycling between input fields, and native focus highlighting.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Integrated debugging\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
:
\f1\b0  Ability to toggle Debug mode and view Prompt results. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Architecture & Workflow
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Frictionless JSON:
\f1\b0  Easy-to-read, easily editable JSON architecture makes reordering rows or regrouping keys a matter of simple copy-and-pasting.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Comment Support:
\f1\b0  Allows standard 
\fs26 //
\fs24  or 
\fs26 ;
\fs24  comments on their own lines within the JSON file for personal notes and documentation.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Pre-Compiled Performance:
\f1\b0  HTML generation is processed independently of the display. This means the HTML file is built in advance, resulting in instantaneous loading when Keyboard Maestro calls the prompt.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Dynamic Variable Injection:
\f1\b0  Automatically pulls values from Keyboard Maestro variables directly into the JSON to dynamically set titles, labels, or input placeholder text.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Visual Error Handling:
\f1\b0  If a JSON syntax error occurs, the script catches it and generates a custom HTML error screen detailing the typo, rather than failing silently.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Known Limitations
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Modifier Whitelisting:
\f1\b0  The UI cannot natively restrict or "block" specific modifiers from being passed through. For example, you cannot prevent 
\f3\fs26 \uc0\u8679 
\f1 R
\fs24  from successfully triggering the 
\fs26 r
\fs24  button. If strict modifier blocking is required, it must be handled via 
\fs26 Switch/Case
\fs24  logic inside the resulting Keyboard Maestro macro.\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \
