\f0\b \cf2 Design Best Practices (Recommended):
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The "Settings" Row:
\f1\b0  For complex prompts, it is highly recommended to include a standardized "Settings 
\f3 \uc0\u8997 
\f1 " row at the bottom of your JSON layout (see \cf3 \cb4 meta.json\cf2 \cb1  for an example). This row should include buttons bound to standard shortcuts to instantly open the JSON file for editing (
\f3 \cf3 \cb4 \uc0\u8997 
\f1 e\cf2 \cb1 ) or trigger the Prompt Initialization subroutine to refresh the HTML (
\f3 \cf3 \cb4 \uc0\u8997 
\f1 r\cf2 \cb1 ).\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Prior to calling the Prompt via HTML Action, option to generate the \cf3 \cb4 <name>.html\cf2 \cb1  file in the same directory.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
