\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 HTML Button Return Specification\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 When an action is triggered within the Custom HTML Prompt, the script passes a single, colon-delimited string back to Keyboard Maestro in the \cf3 \cb4 HTML Result Button\cf2 \cb1  variable.\
The string is formatted as four distinct parts separated by colons: \cf3 \cb4 BaseID:Modifiers:Key:Parameter\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

